items.sentence: Mary couldn't find a dress to wear to the prom.
Mary bought herself a new purse this afternoon.
I really thought that Tom was going to do that.
I'm wondering whether to ask Mary to the dance.
I have no idea when Tom learned how to do that.
Tom made sure that everything was set up right.
I dreamed that I was being chased by a monster.
I keep having the same dream night after night.
Animals can't tell what's real and what's fake.
Better to be a happy fool than an unhappy sage.
